<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-02-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-02-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="79" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d79">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Adams</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Seward</persName>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 600.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United
                                        States,</hi><hi rend="italic"> London,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-02-18"><hi rend="italic">February</hi> 18, 1864.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have the honor to report to you that the
                            British government has very liberally acceded to the application made by
                            Mr. P. McD. Collins, and has granted to him the right to continue his
                            proposed telegraph communication from Russia over the English
                            territorial possessions in Northwestern America. Agreeably to the
                            directions contained in your No. 652, of the 13th of July, 1863, I have
                            done whatever was in my power to facilitate his efforts. Mr. Collins is
                            on his way to America, and will report hi ssuccess to you in person.</p>
                        <p>I have the honor to be, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>CHARLES ERANCIS ADAMS.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward</hi>, <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>